            <div id="id5" style="height: 241px; left: 369px; position: absolute; top: 10px; width: 611px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_1 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_611_241" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <p style="padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style">If I can buy a cup of espresso for a $1.5 the Numeraire is Dollar. If Starbucks starts giving out a $ for ½ a cup of espresso then Numeraire is espresso. So basically it’s just a standard by which values are measured. Generally we are accustomed with lovely green pieces of paper. Since this a quant’s blog let’s move to the mathematics. <br /></p>
